                            <comment id="151577" author="adilger" created="Mon, 9 May 2016 23:09:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Saurabh, could you please submit a patch to remove test 184c from the ALWAYS_EXCEPT list in sanity.sh, with the appropriate &lt;tt&gt;Test-Parameters:&lt;/tt&gt; line to run sanity several times on ZFS to ensure that it is passing reliably.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="95396" author="adilger" created="Wed, 1 Oct 2014 07:16:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;sanity.sh test_184c is still being skipped on ZFS filesystems due to this bug.  If it was fixed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2918&quot; title=&quot;Test failure on test suite sanity&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2918&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2918&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; then a patch should be submitted to re-enable the test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53447" author="jay" created="Wed, 6 Mar 2013 10:53:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Filed &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2918&quot; title=&quot;Test failure on test suite sanity&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2918&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2918&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for this failure.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="53443" author="jay" created="Wed, 6 Mar 2013 10:40:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Obviously this is due to a different issue:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;== sanity test 184c: Concurrent write and layout swap == 01:39:55 (1362476395)&lt;br/&gt;
50+0 records in&lt;br/&gt;
50+0 records out&lt;br/&gt;
52428800 bytes (52 MB) copied, 10.6071 s, 4.9 MB/s&lt;br/&gt;
48+0 records in&lt;br/&gt;
48+0 records out&lt;br/&gt;
50331648 bytes (50 MB) copied, 10.3514 s, 4.9 MB/s&lt;br/&gt;
ref file size: ref1(52428800), ref2(50331648)&lt;br/&gt;
error: cannot open for write /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d184/184c/file1: No such file or directory (2)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For unknown reason it couldn&apos;t open the file for layout swap.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
